Martin C. ANSORGE, as Receiver, etc., Plaintiff-Appellant, v. WESTCHESTER COUNTY, Defendant-Appellee. No. 290. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. March 11, 1936. Compton, Dillon & Clark, of New York City (Murray L. Halpern and Frank J. Dillon, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. William A. Davidson, of Port Chester, N. Y.1 (Frank J. Claydon, of Mt. Vernon, N. Y., of counsel), for appellee.

Before MANTON, L. HAND, and SWAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed in open court.
